On July 18, 1987, soul and R&B performer Curtis Mayfield took to the stage at the famed Montreux Jazz Festival and proved why he had achieved legendary status in such a short time. Catch his renditions of such songs as "Ice 9," "It&#039;s Alright," "Gypsy Woman," "Freddie&#039;s Dead," "Pusher Man," "We Got to Have Peace," "We&#039;ve Only Just Begun," "People Get Ready," "Move On Up," "When Seasons Change" and more.
